@YifanWang-22, you can export the model to fp32 in CPU with large memory using PyTorch.

There is separated python script that could convert ONNX model from FP32 to FP16. The script can run in CPU only: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxconverter-common/blob/master/onnxconverter_common/float16.py

If you want to export huge model in CUDA, you will need some extra work: export your model in several parts.  For example, you can export layer by layer: embedding layer, transformer layer and pooling layer separately. Then have another script to optimize each layer and convert it to FP16, and finally concatenate all layers into one graph.
